         <abstract>
            <p>We consider the approximation of d-dimensional weighted integrals of certain isotropic functions. We are mainly interested in cases where d is large. We show that the convergence rate of quasi-Monte Carlo for the approximation of these integrals is O(<tex-math>$\sqrt {\text{log} n}$</tex-math>/n). Since this is a worst case result, compared to the expected convergence rate O(n<sup>-1/2</sup>) of Monte Carlo, it shows the superiority of quasi-Monte Carlo for this type of integral. This is much faster than the worst case convergence, O(log<sup>d</sup> n/n), of quasi-Monte Carlo.</p>
          </abstract>
